---
description: Next.js App Router and React conventions. Applies to all frontend files.
globs: ["src/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

## Server vs client components
- Default to Server Components — only add `"use client"` when you need:
  - `useState`, `useEffect`, or other React hooks
  - Browser-only APIs (`window`, `document`, `localStorage`)
  - Event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`, etc.)
- Never put `"use client"` at the top of a page — push it down to the
  smallest component that actually needs it.
- Never `fetch` inside a Client Component — pass data as props from a
  Server Component parent.

## Data fetching
- Fetch in Server Components using `async/await` directly — no `useEffect` for data.
- Use `fetch` with Next.js cache options: `{ cache: 'force-cache' }` for static,
  `{ next: { revalidate: N } }` for ISR, `{ cache: 'no-store' }` for dynamic.
- For client-side mutations: use Server Actions, not API routes.
- Never fetch the same data in multiple places — lift to the closest shared Server Component.

## Component structure
- One component per file. File name matches component name in kebab-case.
- Props interface declared above the component: `type [Name]Props = { ... }`.
- Component is a `const` arrow function, not a `function` declaration.

## File locations
- Pages: `src/app/[route]/page.tsx`
- Layouts: `src/app/[route]/layout.tsx`
- API routes: `src/app/api/[endpoint]/route.ts`
- Shared UI components: `src/components/`
- Utility functions: `src/lib/`

## Tailwind
- Utility classes only — no custom CSS files except `globals.css`.
- No arbitrary values (`w-[327px]`) unless absolutely unavoidable.
- Responsive: mobile-first (`sm:` `md:` `lg:`).
- Dark mode via `dark:` prefix — never hardcode colours.
- Class order: layout → spacing → typography → colour → state.
- Extract repeated class combinations into a component, not a `@apply`.

## Error and loading states
- Every page that fetches data needs:
  - `loading.tsx` alongside `page.tsx`
  - `error.tsx` alongside `page.tsx`
- Every async Server Component must handle thrown errors gracefully.
- Empty states are UI — define them in the component, not as an afterthought.

## Performance
- Dynamic import heavy components: `const X = dynamic(() => import('./X'))`.
- Images: always use `next/image` — never `<img>`.
- Fonts: always use `next/font` — never a raw `<link>`.
- `useMemo` and `useCallback` only for demonstrated re-render problems — not pre-emptively.

## Do not
- Do not use `useRouter` for navigation — use `<Link>` from `next/link`.
- Do not use `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps` — App Router only.
